1
00:00:02,302 --> 00:00:03,368
-<i> PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.
<i>- HAVE WE MET?</i>

2
00:00:03,437 --> 00:00:04,803
THOMAS GATES.
FRIENDS CALL ME TOMMY.

3
00:00:04,871 --> 00:00:05,904
I DON'T HAVE ANY FRIENDS.

4
00:00:05,972 --> 00:00:07,739
EVERYTHING THAT
I'VE EVER DONE OR FELT,

5
00:00:07,808 --> 00:00:09,807
IT WAS WASTED BECAUSE
YOU WEREN'T PART OF IT.

6
00:00:09,876 --> 00:00:11,009
THOMAS?

7
00:00:11,078 --> 00:00:14,212
-<i> I FIND IT HARD TO BELIEVE...</i>
- THOMAS?

8
00:00:14,281 --> 00:00:17,282
<i>THAT SOMEBODY BREAKS INTO</i>
<i>YOUR HOUSE, SHOOTS YOUR LOVER</i>
<i>POINT BLANK IN THE HEAD.</i>

9
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:20,753
- OH, MY GOD.
- AT LEAST I KNOW HOW TO
PROTECT THE ONES I LOVE.

10
00:00:20,821 --> 00:00:24,690
<i>THE MAN THE POLICE THINK</i>
<i>KILLED THOMAS GATES DIED</i>
<i>OF A DRUG OVERDOSE IN HIS CELL.</i>

11
00:00:24,759 --> 00:00:28,026
DADDY, THIS MAN
WAS THE LAST LINK IN PROVING
WHO KILLED THOMAS.

12
00:00:28,094 --> 00:00:29,995
I DON'T WANT ANY TRACE
OF CENTRE INVOLVEMENT.

13
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:32,096
<i> THEY KILLED THEM ALL.</i>
<i> AND FOR WHAT?</i>

14
00:00:32,165 --> 00:00:36,501
- WHAT WILL YOU DO NOW?
- FIND OUT WHO DID THIS
AND MAKE THEM PAY.

15
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,810
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>TELL ME ABOUT YOURSELF.</i>

16
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:47,111
- WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?
- EVERYTHING.

17
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:49,814
<i>[ Gates ]</i>
<i>BRIDGET SEEMS LIKE</i>
<i>A NICE PERSON.</i>

18
00:00:51,685 --> 00:00:55,320
IF IT'S MAKING YOU THIS
MISERABLE, MAYBE YOU SHOULD STOP
SPENDING TIME WITH THEM.

19
00:00:55,389 --> 00:00:59,390
- THEY'RE MY FAMILY.
-<i> MAYBE YOU SHOULD THINK</i>
<i> ABOUT STARTING A NEW ONE.</i>

20
00:00:59,459 --> 00:01:02,761
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PLACES IN ME, TOMMY.</i>
<i>DARK PLACES.</i>

21
00:01:02,830 --> 00:01:07,232
<i>IF SOMETHING IS NOT RIGHT,</i>
<i>WE'LL DEAL WITH IT. TOGETHER.</i>

22
00:01:07,301 --> 00:01:09,767
I'M A FIX-IT MAN, REMEMBER?

23
00:01:11,104 --> 00:01:13,038
<i>[ Gates ]</i>
<i>I WILL MAKE YOU A DEAL.</i>

24
00:01:13,106 --> 00:01:16,041
<i>WHEN I DIE,</i>
<i>I'LL LEAVE YOU ALL MY SHIRTS.</i>

25
00:01:16,109 --> 00:01:17,742
<i>HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY.</i>

26
00:01:17,811 --> 00:01:19,977
I'M NOT GOIN' ANYWHERE.

27
00:01:20,046 --> 00:01:22,047
HMM?

28
00:01:43,670 --> 00:01:46,638
<i>[ Shower Water Running ]</i>

29
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:05,990
<i> PARKER?</i>

30
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:13,031
TOMMY.

31
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,599
I LOVE YOU, PARKER.

32
00:02:22,409 --> 00:02:26,411
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>

33
00:02:28,415 --> 00:02:30,348
<i> [ Line Ringing ]</i>

34
00:02:30,417 --> 00:02:32,350
[ Sighs ]
[ Beeps ]

35
00:02:32,419 --> 00:02:35,353
MUST BE THE 10th TIME
I GOT HER PHONE MACHINE.

36
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:38,056
<i> [ Sydney ]</i>
<i> YOU LEFT THE ADDRESS,</i>
<i> DIDN'T YOU?</i>

37
00:02:38,125 --> 00:02:41,059
MAYBE MISS PARKER
WILL MEET US HERE.

38
00:02:41,128 --> 00:02:45,063
SYD, SHE HATES ANYONE
TO ENTER ONE OF JAROD'S LAIRS
BEFORE SHE DOES.

39
00:02:45,132 --> 00:02:47,432
[ Sighs ]
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

40
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,967
<i>SOMETHING'S UP.</i>
THINK BACK ONE YEAR, BROOTS.

41
00:02:52,705 --> 00:02:54,639
THOMAS?
<i>THOMAS?</i>

42
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:59,143
TODAY? IT'S A YEAR TO THE DAY
THAT SHE FOUND THOMAS
MURDERED AT HER HOUSE?

43
00:02:59,212 --> 00:03:02,013
<i>I'M SUCH AN IDIOT.</i>

44
00:03:02,082 --> 00:03:06,151
I LEFT ALL THOSE PHONE MESSAGES
ON HER MACHINE LIKE IT WAS
JUST ANY OTHER DAY.

45
00:03:06,219 --> 00:03:08,220
IT<i> IS</i>
JUST ANY OTHER DAY.

46
00:03:08,288 --> 00:03:10,555
SAME CLOWN.

47
00:03:12,893 --> 00:03:14,492
DIFFERENT SIDE SHOW.

48
00:03:17,731 --> 00:03:20,198
I'M SORRY,
MISS PARKER.

49
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,267
THANK YOU.

50
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:27,438
<i>SO, WHAT'S UP</i>
<i>WITH JAROD THE JESTER?</i>

51
00:03:27,507 --> 00:03:31,510
WELL, SYD AND I HAVE BARELY
SCRATCHED THE SURFACE,
IF YOU WANT TO START DIGGIN' IN.

52
00:03:37,251 --> 00:03:39,417
[ Clears Throat ]

53
00:03:40,753 --> 00:03:43,087
HAVE CLEAN-UP
CRATE EVERYTHING.

54
00:03:43,156 --> 00:03:45,790
<i> IF WE CAN'T FIGURE OUT</i>
<i> WHAT JAROD'S UP TO,</i>

55
00:03:45,859 --> 00:03:48,560
WE CAN DONATE THIS STUFF
TO A TWO-RING CIRCUS
LOOKING TO ADD A THIRD.

56
00:03:48,629 --> 00:03:51,295
WE DID FIND ONE THING.

57
00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:54,466
THE CELEBRITY CLOWN
OF A LOCAL KIDDIE SHOW,
MARCO THE MAGNIFICENT,

58
00:03:54,535 --> 00:03:56,467
WAS ARRESTED YESTERDAY
ON MOLESTATION CHARGES.

59
00:03:56,537 --> 00:03:59,004
POLICE FOUND HIM
LOCKED IN A LION CAGE...

60
00:03:59,073 --> 00:04:01,773
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>
<i>WITH RAW BEEF</i>
<i>STRAPPED TO HIS--</i>

61
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,443
ANYWAY,
WELL, IT'S ALL IN THERE.

62
00:04:05,512 --> 00:04:11,115
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
BOYS AND GIRLS,
I GIVE YOU...

63
00:04:11,184 --> 00:04:12,984
RINGMASTER JAROD.

64
00:04:21,227 --> 00:04:23,161
WHAT IS IT?

65
00:04:23,229 --> 00:04:25,163
IT'S--

66
00:04:25,231 --> 00:04:28,566
IT'S JAROD'S
TWISTED LITTLE MODEL...

67
00:04:28,635 --> 00:04:31,436
OF MY FIRST MEETING
WITH THOMAS.

68
00:04:31,505 --> 00:04:35,807
- BASTARD.
- I'M SURE THERE'S AN INNOCENT
REASON JAROD LEFT IT.

69
00:04:35,876 --> 00:04:38,309
RIGHT.

70
00:04:38,378 --> 00:04:40,912
AND O.J. WAS
JUST CHIPPING GOLF BALLS.

71
00:04:41,748 --> 00:04:43,615
ALL I'M SAYING IS--

72
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:46,617
IT'S BAD ENOUGH HE KNOWS
HOW THOMAS AND I MET, BUT...

73
00:04:46,687 --> 00:04:50,188
THE FACT THAT HE LEFT IT FOR ME
ON THIS DAY IS NO MISTAKE.

74
00:04:50,256 --> 00:04:55,293
<i> FOR ONCE,</i>
<i> ADMIT HE'S TORMENTING ME</i>
<i> JUST TO TORMENT ME.</i>

75
00:04:55,362 --> 00:04:58,363
AND WHEREVER HE IS,
I JUST KNOW HE'S LAUGHING.

76
00:05:18,518 --> 00:05:20,518
[ Nose Squeaks ]

77
00:05:24,090 --> 00:05:26,090
HARDLY LAUGHING.

78
00:05:35,235 --> 00:05:38,369
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>
<i>THERE ARE PRETENDERS AMONG US.</i>

79
00:05:38,438 --> 00:05:40,371
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>I WAS TAKEN FROM MY FAMILY.</i>

80
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:44,008
<i>THIRTY-SIX HOURS AND HE'S</i>
<i>ALREADY DEMONSTRATING MORE</i>
<i>TALENT THAN ANY OF OUR OTHERS.</i>

81
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:47,479
<i>HOW MANY PEOPLE DIED</i>
<i>BECAUSE OF WHAT I THOUGHT UP?</i>

82
00:05:47,548 --> 00:05:50,982
SINCE I BROKE OUT,
I'VE SPENT EVERY MOMENT
SEARCHING FOR MY PAST.

83
00:05:51,051 --> 00:05:53,251
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE'S A PRETENDER--</i>

84
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:56,087
<i>A GENIUS WHO CAN BECOME</i>
<i>ANYONE THAT HE WANTS TO BE.</i>

85
00:05:56,156 --> 00:05:58,156
-<i> THE CENTRE WANTS HIM ALIVE.</i>
- PREFERABLY.

86
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:01,126
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>HE DEFENDS THE WEAK AND ABUSED.</i>

87
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:02,961
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>
<i>LIFE'S A GIFT.</i>

88
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:16,508
-<i> YOU A DOCTOR?</i>
- I AM TODAY.

89
00:06:22,482 --> 00:06:27,385
TO HOUSES
SKILLFULLY TURNED INTO HOMES.

90
00:06:29,155 --> 00:06:33,058
TO EMPTY HEARTS
FILLED UP AGAIN.

91
00:06:34,695 --> 00:06:38,529
TO NEW BEGINNINGS
THAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN.

92
00:06:41,301 --> 00:06:44,803
ALL LEFT WITH YOU, MY LOVE.

93
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:03,120
BEAUTIFUL WORDS.

94
00:07:06,025 --> 00:07:09,728
WHAT, NO CONFETTI GONGS, JOY
BUZZERS, SQUIRTING FLOWERS?

95
00:07:09,796 --> 00:07:12,731
NONE OF THIS
IS A LAUGHING MATTER.
YEAH.

96
00:07:12,799 --> 00:07:15,801
NO, YOU REALLY CAUGHT ME
IN A MOOD TODAY.

97
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:20,572
I'M REAL TEMPTED
TO PUT A CAP IN YOU,

98
00:07:20,641 --> 00:07:25,076
WIPE THE SLATE CLEAN ON MY LIFE
AND TAKE OFF WITHOUT EVER
LOOKING BACK.

99
00:07:25,145 --> 00:07:29,747
YOUR GUN WON'T WORK.
I TOOK THE FIRING PIN OUT
LAST NIGHT.

100
00:07:29,816 --> 00:07:32,516
I SLEEP WITH THIS
UNDER MY PILLOW.

101
00:07:32,585 --> 00:07:35,587
AND YOU DROOL
OUT OF THE LEFT
CORNER OF YOUR MOUTH.

102
00:07:48,434 --> 00:07:51,035
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING HERE, JAROD?

103
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:55,106
IT'S TIME TO TAKE CARE OF
SOME UNFINISHED BUSINESS,

104
00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:58,142
<i> TO FIND OUT WHO KILLED</i>
<i> THE MAN YOU LOVED AND WHY,</i>

105
00:07:58,211 --> 00:08:00,344
AND TO PAY RESPECTS
TO A MAN LIKE THOMAS GATES,

106
00:08:00,413 --> 00:08:02,313
BECAUSE HE DESERVES IT.

107
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:09,654
JUST BECAUSE YOU'RE A GENIUS
DOESN'T MEAN YOU KNOW
WHAT HE DESERVES.

108
00:08:15,895 --> 00:08:18,529
WHY ARE YOU TORMENTING ME,
JAROD?

109
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,232
WHY DO YOU EVEN C-CARE?

110
00:08:34,614 --> 00:08:36,548
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>
<i>RUMOR 5-8-2-5-9?</i>

111
00:08:36,617 --> 00:08:38,983
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>YEAH. STANDARD CENTRE</i>
<i>CODING LOGISTICS.</i>

112
00:08:39,052 --> 00:08:41,920
IN THIS CASE,
"RUMOR" WOULD BE THE CODE NAME
OF THE OPERATIVE IN CHARGE.

113
00:08:41,988 --> 00:08:44,923
AS FAR AS THE NUMBERS,
I'LL HAVE TO TALK TO MANNY.

114
00:08:44,991 --> 00:08:48,392
YOU KNOW THE MUTE GUY
DOWN IN COMMUNICATIONS?
HE, THE ONE WITHOUT A TONGUE?

115
00:08:48,461 --> 00:08:51,328
YEAH. I GUESS IT'D BE PRETTY
POINTLESS TO PLAY SPIN THE
BOTTLE WITH A GUY LIKE THAT.

116
00:08:51,397 --> 00:08:53,398
I MEAN,
IF I WAS A WOMAN.

117
00:08:55,502 --> 00:09:00,137
ANYHOW, OFFHAND I'D SAY
THESE NUMBERS MIGHT BE A CODE...

118
00:09:00,206 --> 00:09:02,674
FOR A CENTRE
AUDIO PHONE TAP FILE.

119
00:09:02,743 --> 00:09:05,243
FIND OUT FROM MANNY
THE MARBLE MOUTH WHICH ONE.

120
00:09:05,311 --> 00:09:09,747
WELL, GIVEN THE CLIMATE AROUND
HERE, MISS PARKER, I DON'T THINK
THAT'S GONNA BE TOO EASY.

121
00:09:09,816 --> 00:09:12,684
- WHY?
- OH, YOU HAVEN'T HEARD?

122
00:09:12,753 --> 00:09:16,888
<i>MUTUMBO'S DEAD,</i>
<i>AS IN "DING-DONG,</i>
<i>THE WICKED WITCH IS."</i>

123
00:09:16,957 --> 00:09:18,923
DEAD.

124
00:09:18,992 --> 00:09:22,460
TRIUMVIRATE'S CRAZY ZULU
APPEARS TO HAVE BEEN MURDERED.

125
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:25,530
<i>[ Mr. Lyle ]</i>
<i>TWO SHOTS THROUGH THE HEART.</i>
SMALL TARGET.

126
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:29,434
AND WHOEVER PUT
THE BULLETS IN MUTUMBO
ALSO GOUGED OUT HIS EYES.

127
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:32,103
LIKE HE SAW SOMETHING
HE WASN'T SUPPOSED TO.

128
00:09:32,172 --> 00:09:36,207
SPEAKING OF WHICH,
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU LAID EYES ON YOUR FATHER?

129
00:09:36,275 --> 00:09:39,744
WHEN IS THE LAST TIME
SOMEBODY CHECKED
FOR YOUR PULSE?

130
00:09:39,813 --> 00:09:41,746
[ Giggling ]
[ Clears Throat ]
UM--

131
00:09:41,815 --> 00:09:43,748
NOW, NOW.

132
00:09:43,817 --> 00:09:49,220
I MERELY ASK BECAUSE FAMILY
IS THE MOST IMPORTANT THING
IN THE WORLD.

133
00:09:49,289 --> 00:09:51,689
MY FAMILY.
YOUR FAMILY.

134
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:53,758
THE CENTRE FAMILY.

135
00:09:54,894 --> 00:09:56,961
CARE TO TRANSLATE
FOR BARNEY THE DINOSAUR?

136
00:09:57,030 --> 00:10:00,464
THE GUN THAT WAS USED
TO KILL MUTUMBO...

137
00:10:00,534 --> 00:10:03,467
WAS TRACED TO THE HIGHEST LEVEL
OF THE CENTRE.

138
00:10:03,536 --> 00:10:07,671
A LEVEL THAT INCLUDES YOU,
MR. LYLE, AND DEAR OLD DAD,

139
00:10:07,740 --> 00:10:12,543
<i>WHO JUST HAPPENS TO GAIN</i>
<i>THE MOST FROM MUTUMBO'S</i>
<i>SUDDEN... ERASURE.</i>

140
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:14,612
YOU THINK
MY FATHER KILLED HIM?

141
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:17,982
ANYONE COULD HAVE.

142
00:10:18,051 --> 00:10:22,019
<i>AFTER ALL,</i>
<i>WHEN WE MISS THE ONES WE LOVE</i>
<i>AND SURVIVAL'S AT STAKE,</i>

143
00:10:22,089 --> 00:10:24,088
WE'RE CAPABLE OF ANYTHING.

144
00:10:25,859 --> 00:10:27,791
TOMMY.

145
00:10:27,860 --> 00:10:30,762
TALK TO ME, PARKER.
THERE'S SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND.
I CAN TELL.

146
00:10:30,831 --> 00:10:33,531
YES. I--

147
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,868
I--

148
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:39,971
IT'S OKAY.

149
00:10:41,374 --> 00:10:44,008
IN YOUR OWN TIME.

150
00:10:44,577 --> 00:10:46,177
MISS PARKER.

151
00:10:46,246 --> 00:10:49,180
THE SEARCH FOR YOUR FATHER
HAS AND WILL CONTINUE
TO INTENSIFY...

152
00:10:49,249 --> 00:10:50,949
ON MY AUTHORITY.

153
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:52,951
HE WILL BE FOUND.

154
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:56,521
AND WHEN HE IS,
THOSE ALLIED WITH HIM...

155
00:10:56,589 --> 00:11:00,391
COULD FIND THEMSELVES
ENDANGERED SPECIES.

156
00:11:09,869 --> 00:11:12,370
HE WAS AS MUCH
AS ACCUSING YOU OF--

157
00:11:12,439 --> 00:11:15,407
HELL, ACCUSING<i> ME</i>
OF PARTICIPATING IN A COUP.

158
00:11:15,475 --> 00:11:18,642
<i>THE LEAST YOU COULD DO</i>
<i>IS PRETEND TO LISTEN. PARKER?</i>

159
00:11:20,013 --> 00:11:21,946
CALL ME...

160
00:11:22,015 --> 00:11:24,949
WHEN YOU'RE BACK
WITH THE LIVING.

161
00:11:26,219 --> 00:11:28,352
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>
<i>DO YOU BELIEVE</i>
<i>IN GHOSTS, SYD?</i>

162
00:11:28,421 --> 00:11:32,189
[ Sydney ]
I BELIEVE IN AN AFTERLIFE.
SECOND CHANCES.

163
00:11:32,258 --> 00:11:36,594
I'M TALKING ABOUT THOMAS.
HIS... PRESENCE
IS ALL AROUND ME.

164
00:11:36,663 --> 00:11:41,433
SOMETIMES I HEAR
MY MOTHER'S WHISPER
OF CONSOLATION,

165
00:11:41,501 --> 00:11:43,434
MY FATHER'S LAUGHTER.

166
00:11:43,502 --> 00:11:46,904
THOSE WE LOVE...

167
00:11:46,973 --> 00:11:49,407
ARE WITH US ALWAYS,

168
00:11:49,476 --> 00:11:51,409
IN LIFE AND DEATH.

169
00:11:51,478 --> 00:11:53,778
IT'S MORE THAN THAT.

170
00:11:53,847 --> 00:11:56,214
I SEE HIM.

171
00:11:56,282 --> 00:11:58,383
ALMOST TOUCH HIM.

172
00:11:59,553 --> 00:12:01,820
THE ANNIVERSARY
OF HIS DEATH.

173
00:12:03,356 --> 00:12:05,457
YOUR FATHER'S DISAPPEARANCE.

174
00:12:05,525 --> 00:12:07,959
NOW MUTUMBO'S ASSASSINATION.

175
00:12:08,027 --> 00:12:12,963
<i> UNDER STRESS, THE MIND</i>
<i> IS CAPABLE OF MANY THINGS.</i>

176
00:12:14,434 --> 00:12:17,368
IT'S NOT MY MIND
PLAYING TRICKS ON ME.
IT<i> IS</i> THOMAS.

177
00:12:17,437 --> 00:12:19,870
HE'S--
HE'S IN THE ROOM WITH ME,

178
00:12:19,939 --> 00:12:22,940
LIKE--
LIKE HE'S WAITING.

179
00:12:23,009 --> 00:12:24,942
<i> MAYBE HE IS.</i>

180
00:12:25,011 --> 00:12:29,380
MAYBE HE'S GIVING YOU
THAT SECOND CHANCE
TO COMPLETE SOMETHING...

181
00:12:29,448 --> 00:12:32,116
LEFT UNFINISHED.

182
00:12:32,185 --> 00:12:33,984
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>

183
00:12:34,053 --> 00:12:36,320
[ Beeps ]

184
00:12:36,389 --> 00:12:38,489
ANGEL.
DADDY?

185
00:12:38,558 --> 00:12:40,491
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

186
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:43,694
<i>BETTER THAN ANYBODY,</i>
<i>NOW THAT MUTUMBO'S, YOU KNOW--</i>
<i>YOU?</i>

187
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:47,465
ME KILL HIM?
IF I HAD, HE'D BE MISSIN'
MORE THAN HIS EYES.

188
00:12:47,534 --> 00:12:49,700
DADDY,
THEY'RE LOOKING FOR YOU.

189
00:12:49,769 --> 00:12:52,236
COX.
LET HIM.
MY COMEBACK PLAN'S WORKIN'.

190
00:12:52,305 --> 00:12:55,239
ONE MORE PIECE,
AND EVERYTHING
WILL BE BACK TO NORMAL.

191
00:12:55,308 --> 00:12:58,943
- YOU SOUND DIFFERENT.
- DAMN STRAIGHT.
I'M GONNA BE A FATHER AGAIN.

192
00:12:59,012 --> 00:13:02,113
I HAVEN'T FELT LIKE THIS
SINCE YOU WERE BORN.

193
00:13:02,182 --> 00:13:04,649
LISTEN,
WE NEED TO HOOK UP.
WHERE?

194
00:13:04,717 --> 00:13:08,452
I HAVEN'T DECIDED.
JUST KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN AND
YOUR BACK COVERED. AND, ANGEL?

195
00:13:08,521 --> 00:13:12,156
THIS TURMOIL?
IT'S ALMOST OVER.

196
00:13:12,225 --> 00:13:15,159
THE SURVIVORS
WILL BE TOGETHER SOON.
[ Line Hangs Up ]

197
00:13:15,228 --> 00:13:17,995
[ Scoffs ]
"SURVIVORS."

198
00:13:21,734 --> 00:13:23,935
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>AS MANNY EXPLAINED TO ME,</i>
<i>THIS CODE--</i>

199
00:13:24,004 --> 00:13:29,774
YOU... HAD A CONVERSATION
WITH A TONGUELESS MUTE?

200
00:13:29,843 --> 00:13:33,477
NO. [ Chuckles ]
NOT IN SO MANY WORDS.
BUT I--

201
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:35,780
BROOTS.
OKAY.

202
00:13:37,917 --> 00:13:39,984
THE PHONE TAP...

203
00:13:40,053 --> 00:13:41,986
WAS ON THOMAS'S PHONE.

204
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:45,790
<i> ALL OF IT WAS ROUTED</i>
<i> TO AN OPERATIVE,</i>
<i> CODE NAME RUMOR.</i>

205
00:13:45,859 --> 00:13:50,395
I STILL HAVEN'T FIGURED OUT
WHO THAT IS YET, BUT I WAS ABLE
TO UNSCRAMBLE PART OF THE CALL.

206
00:13:50,463 --> 00:13:52,363
AND I-I-I DOWNLOADED IT.

207
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:54,698
PLAY IT.

208
00:13:58,972 --> 00:14:03,407
<i>[ Gates ] YEAH. PARKER AND I</i>
<i>ARE GOIN' AWAY FOR THE WEEKEND,</i>
<i>SO WE'LL TALK WHEN I GET BACK.</i>

209
00:14:03,476 --> 00:14:05,409
<i> [ Jarod ]</i>
<i> OKAY, BUDDY.</i>
<i> I'LL SEE YOU AGAIN SOON.</i>

210
00:14:05,478 --> 00:14:07,878
<i>[ Gates ]</i>
<i>YOU TAKE CARE, JAROD.</i>
<i>[ Line Clicks ]</i>

211
00:14:12,752 --> 00:14:15,119
TOMMY AND JAROD...

212
00:14:15,188 --> 00:14:17,188
WERE FRIENDS?

213
00:14:46,153 --> 00:14:48,553
<i>[ Gates ]</i>
<i>TALK TO ME.</i>

214
00:14:48,622 --> 00:14:51,555
[ Exhales ]

215
00:14:51,624 --> 00:14:54,392
<i> [ Shower Faucet Squeaks ]</i>
<i> [ Shower Water Running ]</i>

216
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:56,461
TOMMY?

217
00:15:14,113 --> 00:15:16,113
TOMMY.

218
00:15:16,182 --> 00:15:17,982
[ Both Gasp ]

219
00:15:19,018 --> 00:15:21,419
ANGEL.

220
00:15:21,488 --> 00:15:23,153
OH, GEEZ.

221
00:15:25,558 --> 00:15:28,492
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA HAVE
A TUB BIRTH THERE FOR A SECOND.

222
00:15:28,561 --> 00:15:30,494
YOU OKAY?
YEAH.

223
00:15:30,563 --> 00:15:33,497
YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU JUST SAW A GHOST.
NO. I--

224
00:15:33,566 --> 00:15:37,401
I'M SO GLAD
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT, DADDY.
I'M JUST FINE.

225
00:15:40,506 --> 00:15:43,440
IT'S BRIGITTE
WE NEED TO WORRY ABOUT.
YEAH.

226
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:46,443
CARRYIN' A NEW LIFE.
IT'S GOD'S ULTIMATE CHALLENGE.

227
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:49,446
HOW DID YOU GET HERE?
I DIDN'T SEE YOUR CAR.

228
00:15:49,515 --> 00:15:52,850
UH, WE, UH, HITCHED A RIDE,
CAME UP THE BACK PATH
AND USED THE KEY YOU GAVE US.

229
00:15:52,919 --> 00:15:54,819
DID I?

230
00:15:54,888 --> 00:15:58,789
I NEED A FAVOR.
ANYTHING.
I WANT TO HELP.

231
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:03,528
BOTH OF YOU.

232
00:16:03,596 --> 00:16:06,197
YEAH, GOOD. WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO HELP EACH OTHER.
I GOTTA HAVE YOUR CAR.

233
00:16:06,266 --> 00:16:08,632
<i> HE FOUND A SAFE PLACE</i>
<i> FOR THE BIRTH.</i>

234
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:10,634
YEAH, WE GOTTA KEEP MOVIN'
FOR THE BABY.

235
00:16:10,704 --> 00:16:14,105
AND A DOCTOR WE CAN TRUST
FOR THE DELIVERY.

236
00:16:14,174 --> 00:16:16,107
DADDY.
HMM?

237
00:16:16,176 --> 00:16:18,943
TELL ME WHERE YOU'RE GOING.
PLEASE? I JUST--

238
00:16:19,012 --> 00:16:22,479
I NEED TO BE A PART
OF SOMETHING POSITIVE
RIGHT NOW.

239
00:16:22,548 --> 00:16:24,681
I CAN'T.
IT'S NOT SAFE.

240
00:16:24,750 --> 00:16:29,354
LISTEN, JUST BECAUSE
MUTUMBO'S DEAD DOESN'T MEAN
HIS ORDER TO KILL US IS.

241
00:16:29,422 --> 00:16:32,390
YOU SEE, I THINK
THE HITTER'S REAL CLOSE.

242
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:36,327
I THINK IT'S COX.
WELL, IT'S A PRO,
THAT'S FOR DAMN SURE.

243
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,796
THAT'S WHY
YOU HAVE TO CARRY ON
BUSINESS AS USUAL.

244
00:16:38,864 --> 00:16:43,000
<i>NOW, IT WON'T BE LONG.</i>
<i>I'M JUST ONE PIECE AWAY</i>
<i>FROM BEIN' BACK...</i>

245
00:16:43,069 --> 00:16:44,735
RUNNIN' THE CENTRE.

246
00:16:44,804 --> 00:16:48,872
I CAN GET YOU THAT PIECE
IF YOU JUST--
NO, NO. YOU CAN'T.

247
00:16:48,942 --> 00:16:50,874
I'LL HAVE IT REAL SOON.

248
00:16:50,943 --> 00:16:53,711
NOW, GIVE ME THE CAR KEYS.
COME ON.
THERE.

249
00:17:02,088 --> 00:17:06,056
- YOU TAKE CARE OF THAT BROTHER
OR SISTER OF MINE.
- I WILL.

250
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:08,926
COME ON.
LET'S GO.

251
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:10,928
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>
DADDY?

252
00:17:10,997 --> 00:17:12,530
HMM?

253
00:17:12,598 --> 00:17:15,499
WHAT IS RUMOR 5-8-2-5-9?

254
00:17:15,568 --> 00:17:18,836
BEATS THE HELL OUT OF ME.

255
00:17:18,905 --> 00:17:22,506
RUMOR IS A CODE NAME
FOR THE OPERATIVE
IN CHARGE OF THAT FILE.

256
00:17:22,576 --> 00:17:26,377
THE REST SOUNDS LIKE
A DIGITAL PHONE TAP NUMBER.
YEAH. SEE?

257
00:17:26,446 --> 00:17:29,180
WE GOTTA HELP EACH OTHER.
COME ON.

258
00:17:29,249 --> 00:17:32,516
<i>NOW REMEMBER,</i>
<i>BUSINESS AS USUAL.</i>

259
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,700
<i>[ Mr. Parker ]</i>
<i>REMEMBER, BUSINESS AS USUAL.</i>

260
00:17:49,769 --> 00:17:53,237
<i>[ Brigitte ] RUMOR'S</i>
<i>A CODE NAME FOR THE OPERATIVE</i>
<i>IN CHARGE OF THAT FILE.</i>

261
00:17:53,306 --> 00:17:56,240
<i>[ Gates ] TALK TO ME, PARKER.</i>
<i>THERE'S SOMETHING ON YOUR MIND,</i>
<i>I CAN TELL.</i>

262
00:17:56,309 --> 00:17:59,243
<i>[ Jarod ] IT'S TIME TO FIND OUT</i>
<i>WHO KILLED THE MAN</i>
<i>YOU LOVED AND WHY.</i>

263
00:17:59,312 --> 00:18:02,246
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>

264
00:18:06,986 --> 00:18:08,920
<i> [ Rings ]</i>
<i> [ Click ]</i>

265
00:18:08,988 --> 00:18:12,556
- WHAT?
- LET'S HOPE THERE'S NOT
A DIGITAL TAP ON THIS PHONE.

266
00:18:12,625 --> 00:18:16,160
IT DIDN'T STOP YOU AND TOMMY
FROM BECOMING FAST FRIENDS.

267
00:18:16,228 --> 00:18:19,731
- AT LEAST YOU'VE DECIPHERED
SOME OF WHAT RUMOR MEANS.
- I'M JUST GETTING STARTED.

268
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:22,667
SO WHY NOT
SAVE ME SOME TIME...

269
00:18:22,735 --> 00:18:26,471
AND JUST TELL ME
WHO KILLED HIM?

270
00:18:26,539 --> 00:18:28,172
I DON'T KNOW.

271
00:18:29,342 --> 00:18:31,275
YOU LISTEN TO ME, JAROD.

272
00:18:31,343 --> 00:18:34,345
THE RULES THAT YOU AND I
HAVE BEEN PLAYING BY--

273
00:18:34,413 --> 00:18:39,183
MY INDENTURED SERVITUDE
TO THIS HOUSE OF HORRORS,
YOU SHAKING YOUR FAMILY TREE--

274
00:18:39,251 --> 00:18:42,186
YOU JUST THROW THOSE
THE HELL OUT THE WINDOW
WHEN IT COMES TO THOMAS!

275
00:18:42,255 --> 00:18:44,122
HE IS NOT A GAME!

276
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:47,391
I WOULD NEVER
TREAT HIM LIKE ONE.

277
00:18:47,459 --> 00:18:50,194
DECEPTION WAS NEVER MY GOAL
WITH YOU AND THOMAS.

278
00:18:50,262 --> 00:18:53,831
YOUR GOAL?
WHAT GOAL?

279
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,601
[ Sighs ]
LOVE.

280
00:18:58,771 --> 00:19:01,939
PUTTING YOU TWO TOGETHER WAS
ONE OF THE MOST REWARDING THINGS
I'VE EVER DONE.

281
00:19:02,008 --> 00:19:03,941
PUTTING US TOGETHER?

282
00:19:04,010 --> 00:19:06,310
YOU'RE A LIAR.

283
00:19:06,379 --> 00:19:11,382
WE HAD A CHANCE MEETING
IN BLUE COVE AT A GAS STAT--

284
00:19:16,222 --> 00:19:19,157
YOU DIDN'T MEET HIM
AFTER I DID.

285
00:19:19,225 --> 00:19:21,159
YOU KNEW HIM BEFORE?

286
00:19:21,227 --> 00:19:24,161
<i>THE WAY YOU FELT</i>
<i>ABOUT EACH OTHER</i>
<i>HAD NOTHING TO DO WITH ME.</i>

287
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:27,531
I JUST--
I JUST LIT THE TORCH.

288
00:19:30,937 --> 00:19:34,371
[ Sobs ]
MISS PARKER,
ARE YOU THERE?

289
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,441
[ Sighs ]

290
00:19:38,712 --> 00:19:43,548
[ Sobs ]
TELL ME ABOUT
THE TOMMY YOU KNEW.

291
00:19:43,616 --> 00:19:46,050
WE MET ABOUT A MONTH
BEFORE YOU DID.

292
00:19:46,118 --> 00:19:48,819
I WAS WORKING CONSTRUCTION
FOR ONE OF HIS COMPETITORS--

293
00:19:48,888 --> 00:19:52,522
A GREEDY CONTRACTOR
WHOSE SELFISHNESS
COST A YOUNG MAN BOTH HIS LEGS.

294
00:19:52,591 --> 00:19:54,758
TOMMY HELPED YOU
TAKE HIM DOWN.

295
00:19:54,827 --> 00:19:58,029
- THOMAS WAS BIG
ON DOING THE RIGHT THING.
- YEAH.

296
00:20:00,433 --> 00:20:04,902
I... HAVE TO KNOW
WHO KILLED HIM, JAROD.

297
00:20:04,971 --> 00:20:08,138
AS SOON AS I FIND OUT ANYTHING,
YOU'LL BE MY FIRST STOP.

298
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:12,342
BUT UNTIL THEN,
EVERYTHING INSIDE OF ME
SAYS RUMOR MURDERED THOMAS.

299
00:20:12,411 --> 00:20:15,579
FOLLOW THAT LEAD.
AND, MISS PARKER,
BE CAREFUL.

300
00:20:15,648 --> 00:20:18,349
RUMORS CAN KILL YOU.

301
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:20,784
[ Beeps ]

302
00:20:24,524 --> 00:20:26,457
<i> PARKER?</i>

303
00:20:27,494 --> 00:20:31,261
- TOMMY.
- TIME TO TRUST NOW, PARKER.

304
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:33,597
- BUT--
- NO. TRUST JAROD.

305
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:35,632
TRUST HIM.

306
00:20:46,045 --> 00:20:49,246
<i>[ Broots ]</i>
<i>THAT'S FUNNY.</i>
<i>"CENTRE VOTING BOOTH.</i>

307
00:20:49,315 --> 00:20:53,151
<i>"USE HANDY LEVER</i>
<i> TO VOTE FOR MOST HATED.</i>

308
00:20:53,219 --> 00:20:55,720
"ONE FLUSH, MR. LYLE.
[ Laughing ]

309
00:20:57,357 --> 00:21:01,191
[ Clears Throat ]
"TWO FLUSHES, MR. RAINES.

310
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:03,260
<i>THREE FLUSHES, MR. COX."</i>

311
00:21:03,329 --> 00:21:07,231
HEY, I GUESS
IT'S ANYBODY'S ELECTION.
<i> I'M FLATTERED.</i>

312
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:19,109
<i>BUT I'D HATE TO BE THE ONE</i>
<i>TO HAVE TO COUNT THE VOTES.</i>

313
00:21:19,179 --> 00:21:22,646
[ Urinal Flushes
Three Times ]

314
00:21:22,715 --> 00:21:25,316
WOULDN'T YOU, MR. BROOTS?

315
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:30,821
THERE ARE RUMORS
GOING AROUND, MR. BROOTS.

316
00:21:30,889 --> 00:21:33,257
RUMORS?

317
00:21:34,627 --> 00:21:36,861
WELL, YOU ARE A WASHER,
I HOPE?

318
00:21:37,931 --> 00:21:40,664
OH, YEAH. ALWAYS.
BEFORE AND AFTER.

319
00:21:44,838 --> 00:21:47,037
[ Air Blowing ]

320
00:21:53,379 --> 00:21:57,381
SO, UH-- [ Clears Throat ]
WHAT KIND OF RUMORS?

321
00:21:57,449 --> 00:22:02,386
IT'S FUNNY-- THESE DRYERS
BRING BACK FOND MEMORIES
OF FATHER'S MORTUARY.

322
00:22:02,455 --> 00:22:06,390
<i>WE EMPLOYED SIMILAR DEVICES</i>
<i>IN THE PREPARATION PROCESS.</i>

323
00:22:06,459 --> 00:22:08,392
OH.

324
00:22:08,461 --> 00:22:10,761
HE USED TO
LET ME HELP AFTER SCHOOL.

325
00:22:10,830 --> 00:22:12,830
IF I WAS GOOD.
[ Chuckles ]

326
00:22:16,202 --> 00:22:19,136
I GUESS EVEN THE DEAD
HAVE TO BE CLEAN.

327
00:22:19,205 --> 00:22:23,140
<i> OH, YES, BECAUSE...</i>
<i> CLEANLINESS IS TRUTH.</i>

328
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:26,043
HERE. PLEASE.

329
00:22:26,112 --> 00:22:28,245
<i>[ Air Blowing ]</i>

330
00:22:35,621 --> 00:22:39,056
<i>YOU BELIEVE IN TRUTH,</i>
<i>DON'T YOU, MR. BROOTS?</i>

331
00:22:39,125 --> 00:22:41,091
[ Clears Throat ]
SURE.

332
00:22:42,561 --> 00:22:45,496
[ Sighs ]
SO, UH,

333
00:22:47,867 --> 00:22:51,368
ABOUT THIS RUMOR THING,
I CAN EXPLAIN--

334
00:22:51,437 --> 00:22:54,037
CLEANLINESS IS TRUTH.

335
00:22:55,408 --> 00:22:58,642
BUT THAT--
THAT'S KINDA HOT.
[ Chuckles ]

336
00:22:58,711 --> 00:23:01,044
<i>JUST LIKE THE CREMATORIUM.</i>

337
00:23:05,084 --> 00:23:10,353
NOW, WHAT RUMORS ARE YOU
HEARING, MR. BROOTS?

338
00:23:10,423 --> 00:23:13,257
OH! [ Groaning ]
OH, MY GOD!

339
00:23:13,326 --> 00:23:15,125
[ Screaming ]

340
00:23:16,996 --> 00:23:18,929
[ Sighs ]

341
00:23:18,998 --> 00:23:20,931
OH, THAT FEELS GOOD.

342
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:23,935
SO, BROOTS,
WHAT DID YOU TELL COX?

343
00:23:24,003 --> 00:23:27,371
I SCREAMED AND TOLD HIM
THAT MY HAND WAS FRYING.

344
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:29,974
ABOUT RUMOR!

345
00:23:30,043 --> 00:23:31,943
WELL, AS IT TURNS OUT,

346
00:23:32,011 --> 00:23:34,946
MR. COX WASN'T INTERESTED
IN THE RUMOR FILE AT ALL.

347
00:23:35,014 --> 00:23:37,948
HE JUST KEPT COMING BACK
TO YOUR FATHER.

348
00:23:38,016 --> 00:23:41,418
<i> HIS PERSISTENT INTEREST</i>
<i> IN YOUR FATHER</i>
<i> POINTS TO ONE THING.</i>

349
00:23:41,487 --> 00:23:45,590
YES. THAT COX IS THE HITTER
HIRED BY MUTUMBO
TO KILL DADDY.

350
00:23:45,658 --> 00:23:48,458
AND BRIGITTE, MAYBE,
AS WELL AS THE BABY.

351
00:23:49,996 --> 00:23:52,629
I'M RUNNING OUT OF TIME.
SO IS DADDY.

352
00:23:52,698 --> 00:23:55,665
ANYTHING FURTHER
ON RUMOR, BROOTS?

353
00:23:55,734 --> 00:23:58,135
WELL, I WAS ABLE
TO REACH THE END
OF THE PHONE TAP ARCHIVE.

354
00:23:58,204 --> 00:24:00,437
AND?

355
00:24:00,506 --> 00:24:04,241
NOTHING BUT A TEXT MESSAGE
TELLING ME THE IDENTITY OF
RUMOR IS IN A HARD COPY FILE.

356
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:06,710
- LET'S FIND IT.
- NO, NO. I-I'M WORKING ON IT.

357
00:24:06,779 --> 00:24:09,747
IT'S, UH--
THE FILE'S CALLED A Z3 FILE.

358
00:24:09,815 --> 00:24:11,982
<i> Z3?</i>
<i>YEAH.</i>

359
00:24:12,051 --> 00:24:15,086
<i> DESIGNATES</i>
<i> CONTRACT KILLINGS FOR HIRE.</i>

360
00:24:15,154 --> 00:24:19,589
MAKES IT A LOCK.
THOMAS WAS MURDERED BY SOMEONE
INSIDE THE CENTRE.

361
00:24:24,430 --> 00:24:27,864
<i>[ Miss Parker ] THANKS FOR</i>
<i>LENDING ME YOUR CAR, BROOTS.</i>
<i> NO PROBLEM.</i>

362
00:24:27,933 --> 00:24:30,867
DO YOU WANT ME TO STICK AROUND
AND KEEP YOU COMPANY
FOR A WHILE, MISS PARKER?

363
00:24:30,937 --> 00:24:32,869
MMM, THANKS,

364
00:24:32,939 --> 00:24:35,506
BUT I DON'T FEEL ALONE.

365
00:24:35,575 --> 00:24:39,042
IT MUST BE PRETTY
HARD STILL, THOUGH, HUH?

366
00:24:39,111 --> 00:24:44,615
WHY DOES SOMEBODY HAVE TO DIE
FOR US TO REALIZE ALL THE THINGS
WE NEVER SAID TO THEM?

367
00:24:45,851 --> 00:24:47,851
WELL,

368
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:56,126
I GUESS IT'S 'CAUSE
WE KINDA TREAT LIFE LIKE
A BUG ON THE SIDEWALK.

369
00:24:56,195 --> 00:24:59,629
ALL WE SEE IS A BUG,
NOT A MIRACLE.

370
00:24:59,698 --> 00:25:02,566
AND NO MATTER
HOW HARD WE TRY,

371
00:25:02,634 --> 00:25:04,868
WE USUALLY END UP
STEPPIN' ON IT...

372
00:25:06,205 --> 00:25:09,139
INSTEAD OF
TAKIN' IT INTO OUR HAND.

373
00:25:09,208 --> 00:25:11,942
AND THE LIVING ARE...

374
00:25:12,011 --> 00:25:15,079
LEFT WITH
ALL THE UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

375
00:25:15,147 --> 00:25:16,880
UNTIL WE FINISH IT, YEAH.

376
00:25:17,950 --> 00:25:19,583
YOU KNOW,
BETWEEN THOMAS...

377
00:25:19,652 --> 00:25:22,753
AND EVERYTHING THAT'S
HAPPENING WITH YOUR FATHER,

378
00:25:22,822 --> 00:25:24,588
<i> I JUST WANT YOU</i>
<i> TO KNOW THAT...</i>

379
00:25:25,791 --> 00:25:27,658
I'M HERE FOR YOU,
MISS PARKER.

380
00:25:27,726 --> 00:25:29,660
I-I MEAN,
IF YOU NEED SOMEONE.

381
00:25:29,728 --> 00:25:31,495
I-I MEAN, A FRIEND.

382
00:25:39,739 --> 00:25:41,838
MISS PARKER?

383
00:25:45,611 --> 00:25:48,545
THE Z3 RUMOR FILE?
HOW DID IT GET IN HERE?

384
00:25:48,614 --> 00:25:53,083
<i>IT'S NOT HOW IT GOT HERE</i>
<i>THAT MATTERS. IT'S WHO IT SAYS</i>
<i>IS THOMAS'S KILLER.</i>

385
00:25:53,151 --> 00:25:55,218
WHO?

386
00:25:57,256 --> 00:25:59,856
REVENGE? YOU SHOULD THINK
ABOUT THIS, MISS PARKER.

387
00:25:59,925 --> 00:26:01,959
THINK ABOUT WHAT?
TOMMY WAS MURDERED.

388
00:26:02,027 --> 00:26:04,895
AND HIS KILLER'S GONNA PAY.
THINKING COMPLETED.

389
00:26:07,866 --> 00:26:09,866
MISS PARKER.

390
00:26:36,462 --> 00:26:39,063
GOD HELP US ALL.

391
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:41,932
<i>BE CAREFUL, PARKER.</i>

392
00:26:42,001 --> 00:26:44,301
TOMMY.

393
00:27:14,232 --> 00:27:16,800
OPEN UP, BRIDGET!

394
00:27:16,869 --> 00:27:19,804
[ Groans ]
ANGEL.

395
00:27:19,872 --> 00:27:22,472
- IT'S 4:00 IN THE MORNING.
- WHERE'S BRIDGET?

396
00:27:22,541 --> 00:27:26,342
- OH, GOD, NOW WHERE DID SHE GO?
- DON'T TRY TO COVER FOR HER!
WHERE THE HELL IS SHE?

397
00:27:26,411 --> 00:27:29,346
SHE WAS HERE
WHEN I FELL ASLEEP.

398
00:27:29,415 --> 00:27:33,150
WE HAD TO LEAVE
OUR LAST HIDING PLACE.
DECIDED TO SLEEP IN THE CAR.

399
00:27:33,219 --> 00:27:36,987
- HOW DID YOU FIND US?
- THE CAR HAS A TRACKING SYSTEM.
DAMN IT.

400
00:27:37,056 --> 00:27:41,058
SHE'S BEEN ACTIN' NUTS THE LAST
COUPLE OF WEEKS, DISAPPEARING
FOR HOURS AT A TIME.

401
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:43,894
<i> OH, MY GOD, ANGEL.</i>
<i> SHE COULD BE</i>
<i> HAVIN' THE BABY.</i>

402
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:47,598
ANGEL, WHAT'S HAPPENED?
WHY ARE YOU HERE?
THOMAS.

403
00:27:47,666 --> 00:27:50,000
RUMOR 5-8-2-5-9.

404
00:27:51,470 --> 00:27:54,071
OH, GOD.
BRIGITTE'S RUMOR.

405
00:27:54,139 --> 00:27:56,740
YOU KNEW NOTHING
ABOUT THIS?
OF COURSE NOT!

406
00:27:56,809 --> 00:27:59,710
SHE MUST HAVE BEEN
FOLLOWIN' MUTUMBO'S ORDERS.

407
00:27:59,779 --> 00:28:01,845
SHE KILLED THOMAS.
I'M SO SORRY.

408
00:28:01,913 --> 00:28:04,347
[ Groans ]
SHE'S CARRYING MY BABY.

409
00:28:04,417 --> 00:28:06,683
DADDY, THINK.
WHERE WOULD SHE GO?

410
00:28:06,752 --> 00:28:09,185
NOW THAT MUTUMBO'S DEAD,
SHE'S NOT SAFE ANYWHERE.

411
00:28:09,255 --> 00:28:11,688
NO, EVERYBODY HAS A SAFE PLACE.
THINK.
WHAT?

412
00:28:11,757 --> 00:28:15,659
WELL, THERE WAS A PLACE.
LET'S SEE, IT WAS
IN THE COUNTRY, I THINK.

413
00:28:15,728 --> 00:28:20,864
<i> I NEVER KNEW WHERE.</i>
<i> BUT SHE KEPT A SPARE KEY</i>
<i> IN HER DESK AT THE CENTRE.</i>

414
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:23,366
I'LL FIND IT,
AND I'LL FIND HER.

415
00:28:23,436 --> 00:28:25,936
THEN WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

416
00:28:32,611 --> 00:28:34,544
THINK ABOUT MY BABY!

417
00:28:34,614 --> 00:28:36,847
<i> [ Door Opens, Closes ]</i>

418
00:28:36,916 --> 00:28:38,916
[ Bell Dings ]

419
00:28:43,422 --> 00:28:47,357
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
DOING HERE?
SEARCHING. WHY?

420
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,560
<i> BECAUSE</i>
<i> YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE.</i>

421
00:28:53,932 --> 00:28:56,866
WITH TRIUMVIRATE PRESSURE,
COX HAS CRANKED UP
HIS SEARCH FOR DAD.

422
00:28:56,936 --> 00:28:59,869
AND IF THEY FIND
ANY LINK TO MUTUMBO'S DEATH,

423
00:28:59,939 --> 00:29:02,806
PARKER WILL NOT
BE THE SAFEST SURNAME
TO HAVE AROUND HERE.

424
00:29:02,874 --> 00:29:05,809
SO, WHEN DID YOUR BOY COX
TURN ON YOU?

425
00:29:05,878 --> 00:29:08,545
LIKE I TRIED
TO TELL YOU BEFORE,

426
00:29:08,614 --> 00:29:10,981
ANY LINK BETWEEN COX AND ME
IS A LIE.

427
00:29:11,050 --> 00:29:14,051
I INTEND TO STAY OUT
OF HIS CROSSHAIRS.

428
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:17,120
AND I SUGGEST
YOU DO THE SAME.

429
00:29:20,625 --> 00:29:22,459
[ Bell Dings ]

430
00:29:23,462 --> 00:29:25,662
MISS PARKER?
BROOTS!

431
00:29:25,731 --> 00:29:27,731
MR. COX AND A TEAM
OF SWEEPERS ARE--
I HEARD.

432
00:29:27,799 --> 00:29:31,234
- I NEED YOU TO FIND
SOMETHING FOR ME. A KEY.
- A KEY?

433
00:29:31,303 --> 00:29:33,837
YEAH. A PIECE OF METAL
WITH TEETH ON IT.

434
00:29:33,905 --> 00:29:36,840
YOU KNOW, THOSE OF US THAT HAVE
EVOLVED BEYOND FIRE AND WHEELS
USE IT TO UNLOCK DOORS.

435
00:29:36,909 --> 00:29:38,642
WHERE IS IT?
BRIDGET'S OFFICE.

436
00:29:38,711 --> 00:29:40,077
BRIGITTE?

437
00:29:44,716 --> 00:29:47,717
<i> [ Phone Ringing ]</i>

438
00:29:49,221 --> 00:29:52,522
- WHAT?
- IT WAS YOUR EYES.

439
00:29:52,591 --> 00:29:54,524
WHAT WAS?

440
00:29:54,593 --> 00:29:56,526
WHERE THOMAS
FELT AT HOME.

441
00:29:56,595 --> 00:29:59,930
- DID HE TELL YOU THAT?
- YES, HE DID.

442
00:29:59,998 --> 00:30:03,534
DO YOU THINK HE EVER KNEW
WHAT I REALLY DID?

443
00:30:04,971 --> 00:30:06,971
I DON'T KNOW.

444
00:30:11,076 --> 00:30:13,009
AND TO HIM, THAT WAS LOVE.

445
00:30:13,078 --> 00:30:16,846
HE SAID THE FIRST TIME HE EVER
EXPERIENCED THAT FEELING WAS
WHEN HE LOOKED INTO YOUR EYES.

446
00:30:16,915 --> 00:30:18,849
[ Exhales ]

447
00:30:18,918 --> 00:30:21,551
MISS PARKER?

448
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:25,489
THERE WERE SO MANY TIMES
I WANTED TO TELL HIM,
TO SAY IT TO HIM.

449
00:30:25,557 --> 00:30:27,491
BUT I--

450
00:30:27,559 --> 00:30:29,159
TELL HIM WHAT?

451
00:30:29,228 --> 00:30:31,895
IT'S TOO LATE NOW ANYWAY,
JAROD.

452
00:30:31,964 --> 00:30:35,999
NEVER UNDERESTIMATE
THE IMPORTANCE OF COMPLETING
UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

453
00:30:36,068 --> 00:30:40,938
OH, DON'T YOU WORRY.
BRIDGET WILL KNOW THE IMPORTANCE
OF THAT REAL SOON.

454
00:30:41,006 --> 00:30:43,941
SO, BRIGITTE IS THE ONE
THAT PULLED THE TRIGGER.

455
00:30:44,009 --> 00:30:47,144
LIKE YOU DIDN'T READ
THE RUMOR FILE
YOU LEFT IN MY HOME.

456
00:30:47,213 --> 00:30:49,980
MISS PARKER,
I DIDN'T LEAVE YOU ANY FILE.

457
00:30:50,049 --> 00:30:53,417
WHETHER IT'S LOVE
OR REVENGE,

458
00:30:53,485 --> 00:30:56,753
DON'T LET
UNFINISHED BUSINESS
FINISH YOU.

459
00:30:56,822 --> 00:30:58,322
[ Beeps ]

460
00:31:02,461 --> 00:31:04,462
<i> [ Knocking ]</i>
[ Beeps ]

461
00:31:10,769 --> 00:31:13,703
YOU FOUND IT!
YES. AND WHAT
IT OPENS, I THINK.

462
00:31:13,772 --> 00:31:17,174
YOU SEE, I REALIZED
THAT IF BRIGITTE WAS
INTERCEPTING THOMAS'S CALLS,

463
00:31:17,243 --> 00:31:19,176
SHE HAD TO HAVE
THEM FORWARDED SOMEWHERE.

464
00:31:19,245 --> 00:31:21,511
SO I WENT TO SEE MANNY
TO SEE IF HE COULD
BACKTRACK THE CALLS.

465
00:31:21,580 --> 00:31:23,614
HE OWES ME A FAVOR
'CAUSE I LOANED HIM
MY KARAOKE MACHINE.

466
00:31:23,682 --> 00:31:25,582
FOLLOW THE BOUNCING BALL,
BROOTS.

467
00:31:25,651 --> 00:31:30,020
WELL, ALL THE CALLS
WERE TRANSFERRED TO A CABIN
LESS THAN 20 MILES FROM HERE.

468
00:31:30,088 --> 00:31:32,389
<i> HERE'S THE ADDRESS.</i>

469
00:31:36,128 --> 00:31:39,063
BE SURE AND TELL MANNY THE MUTE
THAT I SAID...

470
00:31:39,131 --> 00:31:41,131
[ Mouths Words ]
"THANK YOU."

471
00:31:48,039 --> 00:31:50,039
[ Engine Off ]

472
00:32:21,840 --> 00:32:24,941
[ Exhales ]
I KNEW YOU'D COME.

473
00:32:28,147 --> 00:32:29,680
I'M HAVIN' THE BABY.

474
00:32:32,585 --> 00:32:34,284
[ Exhales ]

475
00:32:43,495 --> 00:32:46,196
I HEARD A LITTLE RUMOR
ABOUT YOU.

476
00:32:48,033 --> 00:32:50,233
IT'S TRUE.

477
00:32:50,302 --> 00:32:52,569
PULL THE TRIGGER
IF YOU WANT.

478
00:32:52,638 --> 00:32:54,771
GOD KNOWS I DESERVE IT.

479
00:32:54,840 --> 00:32:58,542
YOU... HAVE NO IDEA.

480
00:32:58,611 --> 00:33:01,044
<i>JUST ANSWER ONE QUESTION.</i>

481
00:33:01,113 --> 00:33:03,046
WHY DID YOU KILL TOMMY?

482
00:33:03,115 --> 00:33:05,582
- ORDERS.
- WHO ORDERED IT?

483
00:33:05,651 --> 00:33:08,885
- [ Grunts ]
- TELL ME WHO!

484
00:33:08,954 --> 00:33:10,720
[ Groaning ]

485
00:33:12,658 --> 00:33:14,724
OH, GOD!

486
00:33:14,793 --> 00:33:17,795
HOW FAR APART
ARE YOUR CONTRACTIONS?

487
00:33:17,863 --> 00:33:20,964
LET'S JUST SAY IT WON'T BE LONG
BEFORE YOU'RE A SISTER AGAIN.

488
00:33:21,033 --> 00:33:23,066
<i> DO WHAT YOU WANT</i>
<i> WITH ME.</i>

489
00:33:23,134 --> 00:33:24,969
JUST PLEASE
LET MY BABY LIVE.

490
00:33:25,037 --> 00:33:28,438
OH, YOU'VE ALWAYS HAD A KNACK
FOR STATING THE OBVIOUS.

491
00:33:28,507 --> 00:33:31,141
<i> THE TRUTH IS,</i>
<i> IT DOESN'T REALLY</i>
<i> MATTER ANYWAY.</i>

492
00:33:31,210 --> 00:33:34,711
- THIS BABY WILL EVEN
THE SCORE FOR YOU.
- THE BABY?

493
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:38,248
<i> I HAVE A DISORDER</i>
<i> CALLED PLACENTA PREVIA.</i>

494
00:33:38,317 --> 00:33:42,419
<i> I'LL BLEED TO DEATH</i>
<i> AS THE BABY IS BORN.</i>

495
00:33:43,689 --> 00:33:46,323
[ Groaning, Inhaling ]

496
00:33:47,626 --> 00:33:50,027
<i> [ Groaning, Screaming ]</i>

497
00:33:50,096 --> 00:33:52,095
UH-UH.
I'LL GET HELP.
[ Dialing ]

498
00:33:52,164 --> 00:33:54,097
[ Groans ]

499
00:33:54,166 --> 00:33:57,001
THERE'S NO SIGNAL
OUT HERE.
[ Groaning Continues ]

500
00:33:57,069 --> 00:33:59,302
HOLD ON!
I'LL GET HELP!

501
00:33:59,372 --> 00:34:03,406
- THE LAND LINE WENT DEAD
AFTER I SPOKE TO YOUR FATHER.
- YOU SPOKE WITH DADDY?

502
00:34:03,475 --> 00:34:06,910
HE SAID YOU'D FIND
THE DOCTOR AND BRING HIM.
<i>WHY DID YOU RUN?</i>

503
00:34:06,979 --> 00:34:11,748
<i> I KNEW IT WAS JUST</i>
<i> A MATTER OF TIME BEFORE</i>
<i> YOU FOUND OUT I WAS RUMOR.</i>

504
00:34:11,817 --> 00:34:14,951
AND WITH MUTUMBO'S
HITTER THERE, I RAN,

505
00:34:15,020 --> 00:34:17,954
HOPING TO KEEP THE FOCUS
AWAY FROM YOUR FATHER.

506
00:34:18,023 --> 00:34:21,658
<i> DESPITE WHAT YOU THINK,</i>
<i> I LOVE HIM VERY MUCH.</i>

507
00:34:21,727 --> 00:34:24,160
[ Screaming ]

508
00:34:24,229 --> 00:34:26,663
GOD!
[ Gasps ]

509
00:34:26,732 --> 00:34:28,665
OH! OH!

510
00:34:28,734 --> 00:34:30,634
[ Gasps ]

511
00:34:30,703 --> 00:34:33,436
<i> OH!</i>
<i> THANK YOU.</i>

512
00:34:35,941 --> 00:34:38,541
THANK FOR NOT MAKING ME
DO THIS ALONE.

513
00:34:53,592 --> 00:34:56,593
♪♪ [ Whistling ]

514
00:35:07,272 --> 00:35:10,307
[ Gasps ]
PUTTING IN OVERTIME?

515
00:35:10,375 --> 00:35:12,075
I'M SALARY.

516
00:35:12,144 --> 00:35:14,677
SO IS YOUR FRIEND, MANNY.
THE TONGUELESS ONE?

517
00:35:14,746 --> 00:35:18,414
THE POOR MAN DROOLS
WHEN HE SPEAKS.

518
00:35:18,483 --> 00:35:21,384
SP-SPEAKS?
[ Clears Throat ]

519
00:35:21,453 --> 00:35:23,419
ABOUT YOU, MR. BROOTS.

520
00:35:23,488 --> 00:35:25,055
ME?

521
00:35:25,124 --> 00:35:28,591
NOW, YOU HAVE AN OPPORTUNITY
TO TELL ME WHERE BRIGITTE WENT.

522
00:35:28,660 --> 00:35:32,162
NOW, IF YOU CHOOSE NOT TO
ACCEPT THAT OPPORTUNITY,

523
00:35:32,230 --> 00:35:37,667
YOU COULD FIND YOURSELF HAVING
MORE IN COMMON WITH MUTE MANNY
THAN JUST KARAOKE.

524
00:35:37,736 --> 00:35:41,004
- [ Exhales ]
- SHALL I SING YOU
A TORCH SONG?

525
00:35:42,674 --> 00:35:44,808
HMM?

526
00:35:47,079 --> 00:35:51,414
<i> [ Groaning,</i>
<i> Inhaling, Exhaling ]</i>

527
00:35:51,483 --> 00:35:54,017
STAY WITH ME, BRIDGET.
I'M HERE.

528
00:35:54,085 --> 00:35:56,686
I'M SORRY...

529
00:35:56,755 --> 00:35:59,356
<i> FOR THOMAS.</i>

530
00:35:59,425 --> 00:36:02,626
FOR ALL THE PAIN
I CAUSED YOU.

531
00:36:02,695 --> 00:36:04,428
YOU NEVER ANSWERED MY QUESTION.

532
00:36:05,764 --> 00:36:07,697
I DON'T KNOW WHO.

533
00:36:07,766 --> 00:36:09,699
BUT IT WASN'T
THE TRIUMVIRATE.

534
00:36:09,768 --> 00:36:12,068
<i> IT CAME FROM</i>
<i> INSIDE THE CENTRE.</i>

535
00:36:12,137 --> 00:36:15,038
THEY THOUGHT THAT
YOU WERE LOSING YOUR FOCUS.

536
00:36:15,107 --> 00:36:17,473
<i> OH, GOD!</i>

537
00:36:17,542 --> 00:36:20,811
SOMETHING'S
HAPPENING INSIDE!
<i>WHERE'S DADDY WITH THE DOCTOR?</i>

538
00:36:20,879 --> 00:36:23,146
- STAY WITH ME NOW.
- I'M GONNA FAINT.

539
00:36:23,215 --> 00:36:26,950
NO, YOU'RE NOT. NO--
OH, I CAN SEE THE HEAD.
YOU NEED TO PUSH.

540
00:36:27,019 --> 00:36:28,952
<i>THE HEAD IS BLUE.</i>

541
00:36:29,021 --> 00:36:30,587
I CAN'T.
<i>YOU CAN. PUSH.</i>

542
00:36:30,656 --> 00:36:33,290
THE BABY NEEDS OXYGEN.
PUSH!

543
00:36:33,359 --> 00:36:36,059
HOW BAD AM I?
<i>UH--</i>

544
00:36:36,128 --> 00:36:38,462
UH, THERE'S A LOT OF BLOOD.

545
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:41,164
- I'M NOT GONNA MAKE IT.
- YES, YOU ARE, DAMN IT!

546
00:36:41,233 --> 00:36:44,601
I CAME HERE TO KILL YOU!
I'LL BE THE ONE WHO DECIDES
WHETHER YOU LIVE OR DIE!

547
00:36:44,670 --> 00:36:47,170
- NOW PUSH!
- [ Screaming ]

548
00:36:48,840 --> 00:36:51,742
PUSH! HOLD ON! HELP'S HERE!
<i> [ Helicopter Whirring ]</i>

549
00:36:58,083 --> 00:37:00,917
[ Screaming Continues ]

550
00:37:02,488 --> 00:37:04,688
<i>[ Baby Crying ]</i>

551
00:37:04,756 --> 00:37:07,991
OH! OH!

552
00:37:08,060 --> 00:37:10,360
<i>[ Crying Continues ]</i>

553
00:37:10,429 --> 00:37:12,963
BRIGITTE?

554
00:37:13,032 --> 00:37:14,964
BRIGITTE!

555
00:37:15,034 --> 00:37:17,034
[ Sobbing ]

556
00:37:25,978 --> 00:37:28,846
OH, GOD. OH.

557
00:38:19,931 --> 00:38:22,699
<i> [ Lock Rattling ]</i>

558
00:38:28,907 --> 00:38:32,675
- I SEE I'M TOO LATE
FOR THE LAMAZE.
- BUT NOT TOO LATE TO DIE.

559
00:38:33,845 --> 00:38:36,746
<i>NO, NO, ANGEL.</i>
<i>HE'S ON OUR SIDE.</i>

560
00:38:38,016 --> 00:38:41,718
UH, DR. COX
IS HERE FOR THE BABY.

561
00:38:41,787 --> 00:38:44,720
- DOCTOR?
- OB-GYN, HARVARD '93.

562
00:38:44,789 --> 00:38:46,523
[ Scoffs ]

563
00:38:46,592 --> 00:38:48,725
MMM.

564
00:38:48,794 --> 00:38:50,927
[ Coos ]

565
00:38:52,497 --> 00:38:54,698
AHH.

566
00:38:54,767 --> 00:38:57,233
OOH. AHA.

567
00:38:57,303 --> 00:38:59,035
THIS SEALS IT.

568
00:38:59,104 --> 00:39:00,870
THE LAST PIECE.

569
00:39:02,641 --> 00:39:05,108
[ Chuckles ]
HERE YOU ARE, NURSE.

570
00:39:05,177 --> 00:39:08,144
<i> DON'T FORGET THE PLACENTA</i>
<i> AND CORD BLOOD.</i>

571
00:39:09,148 --> 00:39:10,647
DADDY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

572
00:39:10,715 --> 00:39:13,049
MR. COX HAS BEEN
MY INSIDE MAN FOR MONTHS,

573
00:39:13,118 --> 00:39:16,819
<i>WATCHING OUT</i>
<i>WHILE I PLANNED MY RETURN.</i>

574
00:39:16,888 --> 00:39:19,289
<i> THERE'S ONLY ONE REASON</i>
<i> FOR YOU BEING HERE, ANGEL.</i>

575
00:39:19,358 --> 00:39:22,425
DID SHE ADMIT TO EVERYTHING
IN THE RUMOR FILE?

576
00:39:22,494 --> 00:39:25,595
DAMN LUCKY THING,
THAT FILE SHOWIN' UP.

577
00:39:25,664 --> 00:39:28,999
- SHE'S GONE.
- MMM.

578
00:39:30,202 --> 00:39:33,002
- DID YOU--
- KILL HER? NO.

579
00:39:34,373 --> 00:39:36,640
SHE DIED IN CHILDBIRTH.

580
00:39:37,809 --> 00:39:40,310
AREN'T YOU EVEN CONCERNED
ABOUT YOUR WIFE?

581
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:43,479
TILL DEATH DO US PART.

582
00:39:43,548 --> 00:39:46,215
WHAT--

583
00:39:46,284 --> 00:39:51,288
SHE WAS NOTHING MORE
THAN A VESSEL FOR THE BABY,
FOR YOUR LEGACY.

584
00:39:55,493 --> 00:39:58,595
DID YOU LEAVE THE RUMOR FILE
IN MY HOUSE?

585
00:39:58,663 --> 00:40:01,598
NOW, WHY WOULD I
DO A THING LIKE THAT?

586
00:40:02,734 --> 00:40:06,369
LET ME GUESS.
THE GUN THAT KILLED MUTUMBO.

587
00:40:06,438 --> 00:40:10,006
FOUND ON HER BODY.
JUST CLEARS EVERYONE
OF EVERYTHING.

588
00:40:10,075 --> 00:40:12,508
SHE PLANTED IT IN MY STUFF!

589
00:40:12,578 --> 00:40:15,579
IT WAS A SETUP.
RUMOR WAS TRYIN' TO
RUIN BOTH OF US.

590
00:40:15,647 --> 00:40:18,514
WHEN ARE THEY GONNA LEARN
THEY CAN'T WHIP
A PARKER, HUH?

591
00:40:19,618 --> 00:40:21,785
MAKE IT ALL GO AWAY.

592
00:40:24,089 --> 00:40:26,389
- DADDY?
- WHAT?

593
00:40:26,457 --> 00:40:28,959
DON'T YOU EVEN WANT TO KNOW?

594
00:40:29,027 --> 00:40:30,693
KNOW WHAT?

595
00:40:33,731 --> 00:40:36,699
IF IT'S A BOY OR A GIRL.

596
00:41:11,370 --> 00:41:15,938
<i>I THOUGHT THAT GETTING REVENGE</i>
<i>FOR TOMMY'S DEATH</i>
<i>WOULD SOMEHOW BRING ME PEACE.</i>

597
00:41:16,008 --> 00:41:20,243
<i>BUT EVEN IF I HAD BEEN ABLE TO,</i>
<i>I KNOW NOW IT WOULDN'T HAVE.</i>

598
00:41:20,312 --> 00:41:24,680
[ Jarod ] THAT ISN'T
THE UNFINISHED BUSINESS
THAT NEEDS FINISHING.

599
00:41:24,749 --> 00:41:28,284
YOU SAID THE OTHER DAY
THAT YOU WISH YOU HAD TOLD HIM.

600
00:41:28,353 --> 00:41:30,287
TOLD HIM WHAT?
I NEVER--

601
00:41:30,355 --> 00:41:33,056
I NEVER TOLD TOMMY
THAT I LOVED HIM.

602
00:41:33,125 --> 00:41:37,427
AND NOW YOUR HEART
AND YOUR MIND ARE RAGING
A WAR AGAINST EACH OTHER.

603
00:41:37,496 --> 00:41:41,030
I WOULD TRADE EVERYTHING
FOR ONE MINUTE WITH HIM.

604
00:41:42,767 --> 00:41:45,702
JUST TO SAY THOSE WORDS
AND HAVE HIM HEAR THEM.

605
00:41:45,771 --> 00:41:47,503
TELL HIM.

